    "result": {"data":{"challengeNode":{"challenge":{"videoId":null,"videoLocaleIds":null,"bilibiliIds":null,"title":"Task 14","description":"<section id=\"description\">\n<p>Demonstrative pronouns such as <code>this</code>, <code>that</code>, <code>these</code>, and <code>those</code> are used to point out specific things or people. <code>This</code> and <code>these</code> refer to objects that are near the speaker. <code>This</code> is used for singular items, and <code>these</code> for plural. <code>That</code> and <code>those</code> refer to objects farther away, with <code>that</code> used for singular and <code>those</code> for plural.</p>\n<p>Examples:</p>\n<p><code>This is my book.</code> (Refers to a book close to the speaker)</p>\n<p><code>That is a car.</code> (Refers to a car that is farther away from the speaker)</p>\n<p><code>These are my friends.</code> (Refers to friends who are close to the speaker)</p>\n<p><code>Those are the mountains.</code> (Refers to mountains that are far from the speaker)</p>\n</section>","challengeType":19,"helpCategory":"English","superBlock":"a2-english-for-developers","block":"learn-how-to-use-code-related-concepts-and-terms","fields":{"slug":"/learn/a2-english-for-developers/learn-how-to-use-code-related-concepts-and-terms/task-14","blockName":"learn-how-to-use-code-related-concepts-and-terms","tests":[]},"question":{"text":"<p>Which sentence uses a demonstrative pronoun correctly?</p>","answers":[{"answer":"<p><code>This are my shoes.</code></p>","feedback":"<p><code>This</code> is singular but <code>my shoes</code> are plural. The correct word should be <code>these</code>.</p>"},{"answer":"<p><code>Those is a bird.</code></p>","feedback":"<p><code>Those</code> is plural but <code>a bird</code> is singular. The correct word should be <code>that</code>.</p>"},{"answer":"<p><code>That are the keys.</code></p>","feedback":"<p><code>That</code> is singular but <code>the keys</code> are plural. The correct word should be <co